<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>go home • go in a home</xh5><p> <i>go home</i>—(also: get home) become quite clear to a person: His calculated sarcasm <u>went home</u> like the sharp point of a rapier.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not fully correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>come home</b>—1. <i>= go home: </i>The ideal of equality would <u>come home</u> with special meaning to men bred up on the frontier. 2. <i>(also: come home to roost)</i> return by way of retribution: Eventually every single problem you have avoided dealing with will <u>come home</u>.</p><p> <i>go in a home—</i>move into an institution such as old people’s home, providing refuge and care: My personal experience with my father was, he was adamant he did not want to <u>go in a home</u>.</p></entry>
